Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Southern Copper, Candente, Relapasa

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-11T21:22:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/peru-stocks-buenaventura-southern-copper-candente-relapasa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rose for the first day this week,
adding 0.7 percent to 21,784.13. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index
gained 1.5 percent to 2,984.56.  Gold and copper miners gained after metals rebounded in New
York and  London , said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-based
brokerage Coril SAB.    Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, rose for the first day in six, gaining 8 percent to
$1.90. Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, rose 3.6 percent to $43.60.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper producer,
gained 2.8 percent to $39.80.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a
Canadian gold exploration company, advanced 1.7 percent to
$2.39.    Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial services
company, gained 1.5 percent to $107.50 after its Banco de
Credito unit sold $700 million of five-year bonds today.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA, fell for a fourth session, losing 1 percent to
1.94 soles after crude slumped in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  